## 1. What Is This Project?

The **Pokemon Pack Simulator** is a desktop app that lets users virtually open Pokemon Trading Card Game (TCG) packs. You select a set, click "Open Pack," and the app gives you a randomized 10-card pack pulled from that set's real card list using simulated rarity odds. You can track your collection in inventory profiles, see how many packs you've opened, and monitor your progress toward completing a set.

The app runs as a native Windows desktop program (no browser, no internet required) built with React/TypeScript for the UI and Rust (Tauri) for the native shell. All data is stored locally on the user's machine. There is no server, no database, and no online component.

