## 4. Pack Structure — How It Works

Every pack generates **10 cards** from a fixed slot layout defined in `DEFAULT_PACK_CONFIG`:

| Slot | Count | What It Pulls From |
|---|---|---|
| Commons | 5 | Common card pool |
| Uncommons | 3 | Uncommon card pool |
| Reverse Holo | 1 | 60% Common / 30% Uncommon / 10% Rare or Holo Rare |
| Rare Slot | 1 | See odds table below |

### Rare Slot Odds (applied to all sets):

| Pull Type | Odds |
|---|---|
| Secret Rare / Rainbow Rare / Special Full Art | 1% |
| VMAX | 10% |
| V | 18% |
| Holo Rare | 21% |
| Standard Rare (non-holo) | 50% |

If a roll lands on a type that doesn't exist in a set (e.g., VMAX in Base Set), the code falls back down the chain to the next available type. V and Secret Rare rolls also cascade down to Standard Rare when higher pools are empty.

### Duplicate Prevention

The simulator tracks which card numbers have already been placed in the current pack and excludes them from subsequent draws. No card number will appear twice in the same pack.

