## 6. Simulator Logic Findings — Detailed Audit

### 6a. CAN ALL CARDS IN A SET BE PULLED? ✅ With Exceptions

**Evolving Skies:** Yes, all 237 cards can theoretically be pulled.
- Commons/Uncommons: Pulled in the common/uncommon slots or reverse holo slot.
- Regular V cards (#7–165 range, "Holo Rare" + V variant in JSON): Correctly mapped to V type → pulled in the rare slot at the 18% V rate.
- Full Art V cards (#166–198, "Ultra Rare" + V variant): Also correctly mapped to V type → pulled in the rare slot.
- Trainer Full Art cards (#199–203, "Ultra Rare" + no variant): Correctly mapped to Secret Rare tier → pulled at 1% in rare slot.
- Rainbow Rares / Special Full Arts (#204–225): Mapped to their respective high-rarity types → pulled at 1% in rare slot.
- Gold Secret Rares (#226–237, "Rare Secret"): Mapped to Secret Rare → pulled at 1% in rare slot.

**Base Set:** **3 energy cards are missing from the JSON data.** The JSON contains energy cards #097 (Fighting), #099 (Grass), and #101 (Psychic) but is missing #098 (Fire Energy), #100 (Lightning Energy), and #102 (Water Energy). These three cards cannot be pulled. The declared `baseSetSize` of 102 is also misleading since only ~99 cards are present.

### 6b. ARE CARDS PULLING FROM THE RIGHT SLOT? ✅ Mostly Yes

Card-to-slot routing is logically correct:
- Commons only appear in common slots or the reverse holo slot (as a reverse).
- V and VMAX cards **never** appear in the reverse holo slot (they are excluded from the reverse-eligible pool). ✅
- Holo Rares correctly only appear in the rare slot (as a Holo) or the reverse slot (as a Reverse Holo version). ✅
- Secret Rares only appear in the rare slot. ✅

One nuance: in Evolving Skies, the **regular numbered V cards** (e.g., #007 Leafeon V) and the **Full Art V cards** (#166 Leafeon V alternate art) both land in the same `vs` pool. This means both versions compete equally for the 18% V slot. In the physical game, Full Art Vs have a lower individual pull rate than their base-numbered counterparts. The sim doesn't replicate this distinction, but both cards are pullable and the overall V percentage is maintained.

### 6c. ARE THE ODDS CORRECT? ⚠️ Major Issue for Base Set / Jungle / Fossil

**For Evolving Skies:** The odds are reasonable approximations of real Sword & Shield era pull rates. Real EVS pull rates are not officially published, but 1% Secret, ~10% VMAX, ~18% V, ~21% Holo, ~50% Rare is a well-accepted community estimate.

**For Base Set, Jungle, and Fossil: The odds are wrong.**

All four sets share the same `DEFAULT_PACK_CONFIG`, which was designed for the modern Sword & Shield era. The original WotC-era sets (Base Set through Fossil, 1998–2001) had a fundamentally different pack structure:

| Characteristic | WotC Era (Base/Jungle/Fossil) | S&S Era (EVS) — *What the sim uses* |
|---|---|---|
| Rare slot: Holo odds | ~50% | **21%** ← too low |
| Rare slot: Non-holo odds | ~50% | **79% effectively** ← too high |
| Reverse Holo Slot | **Does not exist** | ✅ always present ← wrong |
| V / VMAX pulls | Does not exist | Falls back correctly to Rare |
| Pack size | 11 cards | 10 cards |

**Practical impact:** When opening a Base Set pack, you should get a Holo Rare (Charizard, Blastoise, etc.) about 50% of the time. The current sim gives you a Holo only 21% of the time. Additionally, every Base Set/Jungle/Fossil pack incorrectly contains a physical Reverse Holo card — a mechanic that didn't exist in those sets.

