## 7. Additional Known Issues

### 7a. Simulation Script Diverges From App Logic
The file `simulate-1000-packs.mjs` is a standalone test script that does NOT match the main app's rarity mapping. In the script, all Holo Rares are lumped into the generic "Rare" pool with no Holo distinction. The script also has no `holoRares` pool. CSV outputs from this script should not be used to validate actual simulator behavior.

### 7b. Pack Score Tiers Don't Apply Equally Across Sets
The scoring system (Bulk → GOD PACK) was designed around Sword & Shield rarities. A Base Set pack, which has no V, VMAX, or Secret Rare pulls, can never realistically exceed a "Good Pack" score. The highest possible score for a Base Set pack is roughly 12 (one Holo Rare) + a few points for commons/uncommons ≈ 20–25 pts, which only reaches "Standard Pack" or borderline "Good Pack." This is functional but may feel deflating for users opening vintage sets.

### 7c. No Per-Set Pack Configuration in JSON Files
The JSON set format does not include a `packConfig` field. While the internal `ActiveSet` data structure supports a custom pack config, there is currently no way to define different odds or slot layouts per set at the data level. Adding WotC-era-correct odds for Base Set/Jungle/Fossil will require either a code-level per-set config map or a JSON schema extension.

